Where yi is the measurement of tree i, a is the mean intercept, b is the mean slope, xi is the d.b.h. or age of tree i, is the random error for tree i with j ~N(0,σ2), σ2 is the variance of the random error, and wi is a known weight that takes on one of the following forms: wi = 1, wi = 1/√xi , wi = 1/xi , wi = 1/x2.
Analysis was conducted using SAS® 9.2 MIXED procedure (SAS 2008). The
bias-corrected Aikaike’s information criterion (AICc) was used to compare and rank the models because of smaller sample sizes (Akaike 1974). The models with
the “best” fit as indicated by having the smallest AICc were selected. Additional steps were needed to obtain comparable AICc values for log-log and exponential models (eqs. 7 and 8). Otherwise AICc values would not be comparable across all models. Multiplying by the geometric mean allows the AICc values to be compared with the models where yi is not transformed (Draper and Smith 1998).

