15. Setback—distance from the tree to the nearest air conditioned/heated space (be aware that this may not be the same address as the tree location). Evaluate as: 1 = 0 to 8 m 2 = 8.1 to 12 m 3 = 12.1 to 18 m 4 = >18 m Use: assess effects of shade on energy use.
16. TreeOr—Tree orientation—taken with compass, as in figure 14 the coordinate of tree taken from imaginary lines extending from walls of the nearest conditioned space (heated or airconditioned space—may not be same address as tree location):
17. CarShade—Number of autos where any portion of any parked automotive vehicle is under the tree’s drip line. Car must be present: 0 = no autos 1 = one auto 2 = two autos, etc. Use: vehicle hydrocarbon emissions reduction.
